, "text_bw": "kalobahN", "text_ar": "كَلْبَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sajodapN", "text_ar": "سَجْدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) because it has the former of the dims. mentioned below, and the first of the pls. mentioned below, with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h", "text_ar": "ه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, *) and it is sometimes pronounced"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$fhp", "text_ar": "شفهة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (T, TA;) or, as some assert, the deficient letter is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "w", "text_ar": "و"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb,) the word being originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afowapN", "text_ar": "شَفْوَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ahowapN", "text_ar": "شَهْوَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) because it has the last of the pls. mentioned below, (S, [but omitted in one of my copies,] and Msb, *) and the latter of the two dims. mentioned below; (Msb;) both of which assertions are stated on the authority of Kh; (IF, Msb;) [The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lip"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a human being;]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afataA AlA_inosaAni", "text_ar": "شَفَتَا الاـِنْسَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the two covers of the mouth of the human being:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) it is [properly] only of a human being: (Msb:) but it is sometimes, metaphorically, of the horse: and in like manner, of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dalow", "text_ar": "دَلْو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or leathern bucket] as used by A'Obeyd; but ISd has expressed a doubt whether he had heard this from the Arabs: (TA:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ifaAhN", "text_ar": "شِفَاهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K, &c.) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afahaAtN", "text_ar": "شَفَهَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, Msb, TA) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afawaAtN", "text_ar": "شَفَوَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Lth, S, Msb, K,) the second of which is said by Lth to be more agreeable with analogy than the third, though the third is more common, as being likened to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanawaAtN", "text_ar": "سَنَوَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sanapN", "text_ar": "سَنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Az, (Msb, TA:) and Ks mentions the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~ahu", "text_ar": "اـِنَّهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lagaliyZu Al$ifaAhi", "text_ar": "لَغَلِيظُ الشِفَاهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily he is thick in the lip"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], as though the term"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afapN", "text_ar": "شَفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to every portion of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$afap", "text_ar": "شَفَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) the dim. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ufayohapu", "text_ar": "شُفَيْهَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ufay~apN", "text_ar": "شُفَيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "humo A^aholu", "text_ar": "هُمْ اَهْلُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~afapi", "text_ar": "الشَّفَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They are those who have the right of drinking with their lips"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi$ifaAhihimo", "text_ar": "بِشِفَاهِهِمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and of watering their beasts."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "binotu $afapK", "text_ar": "بِنْتُ شَفَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "